55. The engraved portraits ofJohnston, contained in his Poemata Omnia and in two editions of the Poetarum Scotorum Musae Sacrae, are mentioned under Nos. 15, 21 and 23. These cannot be said to bear much resemblance to either of the paintings now extant. The frontispiece of the Poemata Omnia is shewn in one of the glass cases in the Scottish National Portrait Gallery.
